# InstanceDepth — Phase 3: Occlusion-Aware Depth Refinement (Sec. 4.2.2)

Refines instance depth layers in occluded regions by reasoning over (main, guest)
occlusion pairs. Completes the InstanceDepth modeling pipeline.

## Module map
| File | Role | Key shapes |
|---|---|---|
| `models/refine/pair_selection.py` | filter (cls>0.9, mask>0.8), IoU>0.1, nearest-depth guest | pairs (P,2) |
| `models/refine/roi_extract.py` | ROIAlign F_obj + geometric priors G_obj | F_obj (P,2,C,7,7), G_obj (P,2,4,7,7) |
| `models/refine/relation_reason.py` | Φo MLP, Eqs. 8–9 | d_hat (P,2), e_obj (P,2) |
| `models/refine/occlusion_refine.py` | orchestrator + composite | refined_depth (B,1,H,W) |
| `losses/refine_losses.py` | L_obj (SigLog), L_dist (Eq.11), L_ref (Eq.12) | scalars |

## Pipeline (per image)
1. **Filter**: category conf (max foreground softmax) > 0.9 AND mask conf (mean sigmoid inside mask) > 0.8.
2. **Overlap**: pairwise mask IoU > 0.1.
3. **Guest**: among overlaps, the instance nearest in depth → guest; the anchor → main.
4. **ROIAlign**: pool depth feats (F_obj) and priors (mask logits, normalized coords, init depth) per box.
5. **Reason**: `E_obj = σ(Φo([F_obj, G_obj]))` (Eq.8); `D̂ = (E_obj·2−1)·D̄ + D_obj` (Eq.9).
6. **Composite**: write the refined layer delta back inside each instance mask.

## Losses
- `L_obj = SigLog(D̂, DT)` (Eq.10) — scale-invariant log on refined instance depths.
- `L_dist = mean ||(D̂_i−D̂_j)² − (DT_i−DT_j)²||` over each main/guest pair (Eq.11).
- `L_ref = λ1·L_obj + λ2·L_dist` (Eq.12).

## Computational complexity
- Filtering: O(N·Hf·Wf). IoU matrix: O(M²·Hf·Wf), M = survivors (≪ N).
- ROIAlign: O(P·C·Hp²·s²). Φo: O(P·(C+Cg)·Hp²·width). All ≪ DINOv2 backbone.

## Confidence labels
- **[Paper Specified]**: thresholds 0.9/0.8/0.1, nearest-depth guest, F_obj∈R^{2×C×Hp×Wp}, G_obj contents, Eqs. 8–12, ROIAlign.
- **[Reasonable Assumption]**: Hp=Wp=7; mask/category confidence definitions; D_obj=depth layer, D̄=same as correction scale; Φo=3-layer MLP; L_dist averaged over pairs; composite via mask delta.

## Verified
6 pairs/image selected on forced overlaps; ROIAlign + Φo + all losses run; full
backward with gradients into every refinement parameter; no-pair edge case leaves
depth unchanged with zero loss. Random-init backbone (no weight download).
